document.title: API Reference
document.description: A quick look at all the available API endpoints.

body.raw:
# API Reference

### Endpoint: `/get-data`

- **Method**: `GET`
- **Description**: Fetches the data from the server.

### Endpoint: `/post-data`

- **Method**: `POST`
- **Description**: Submits data to the server.
body.html:
API Reference

Endpoint: /get-data

  • Method: GET
  • Description: Fetches the data from the server.

Endpoint: /post-data

  • Method: POST
  • Description: Submits data to the server.

document.title: Installation
document.description: How to install the library in your project.

body.raw:
# Installation Guide

Follow these steps to set up the library in your project:

1. Run `npm install my-library`.
2. Import the library using `import { MyLibrary } from 'my-library'`.
body.html:
Installation Guide

Follow these steps to set up the library in your project:

  1. Run npm install my-library.
  2. Import the library using import { MyLibrary } from 'my-library'.
